ExampleSeriesOrEntity: FNMA 3.0 2043 CUSIP; Freddie Gold; Ginnie II; non agency RMBS bond
Description: Tradeable fixed income instruments backed by mortgage collateral, including agency pass throughs and non agency RMBS bonds.
KeyAttributes: cusip; isin; ticker; security_type; agency_flag; coupon; issue_date; maturity_date; day_count; payment_frequency
TypicalSources: Fannie Mae; Freddie Mac; Ginnie Mae disclosure; TRACE; Bloomberg; Refinitiv
Comments: Free for internal use, need a commercial license for external distribution (starts at 10k each)

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Bloomberg US MBS index; Bloomberg Agg; custom cohort index
Description: Benchmark indices that group MBS or broader fixed income securities into a defined basket used for performance comparison and risk management.
KeyAttributes: index_id; name; family; methodology; rebal_frequency
TypicalSources: Bloomberg indices; other index vendors
Comments:
Requires Bloomberg Terminal + Desktop API for early-stage internal use
Will need a Bloomberg data license (likely per security for commercial use)

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Private label RMBS 2024-1; Fannie REMIC trust
Description: Legal securitization deals or trusts that issue one or more tranches backed by a pool of mortgage loans.
KeyAttributes: deal_id; name; closing_date; issuing_entity; deal_type; collateral_type
TypicalSources: Trustee reports; offering circulars; Intex; Andrew Davidson; Yield Book

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Class A1; M2; B1; IO strip; PO strip
Description: Individual bond classes within a securitization that have distinct cashflow priorities and risk profiles (principal, interest only, etc).
KeyAttributes: tranche_id; class_name; coupon; notional; WAL; credit_support; payment_rules
TypicalSources: Deal docs; trustee reports; Intex; Andrew Davidson; Yield Book

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Fannie pool 123456; Ginnie pool MA1234
Description: A pool of mortgage loans whose cashflows are aggregated to back one or more MBS securities.
KeyAttributes: pool_id; pool_type (single_family/multi); orig_balance; current_balance; WAC; WAM; WALA; loan_count; agency
TypicalSources: GSE and Ginnie pool disclosure and factor files
Comments: Free for internal use, need a commercial license for external distribution (starts at 10k each)

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: FNCL 6.0 Jan 2025; FGLMC 4.5 Feb 2025
Description: Standardized forward contracts for delivery of eligible MBS pools at a future settlement date, used to hedge and trade generic mortgage exposure.
KeyAttributes: product (FNCL/FGLMC/GNMA2); coupon; settlement_month; settlement_date; contract_standard
TypicalSources: Dealer feeds; Bloomberg; Tradeweb

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Security included in index at a date
Description: Relationship node or edge capturing that a given security is part of a specific index on a given date, with an associated weight.
KeyAttributes: index_id; security_id; weight; inclusion_date; exclusion_date
TypicalSources: Index provider data

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Individual residential mortgage backing a pool
Description: Underlying mortgage obligation of a borrower, with detailed underwriting terms and borrower attributes that drive credit and prepayment risk.
KeyAttributes: loan_id; orig_balance; current_balance; note_rate; orig_date; maturity_date; amort_type; product_type; purpose; channel; documentation; FICO; LTV; DTI; occupancy; state
TypicalSources: Fannie loan level disclosure; Freddie loan level; non agency loan tapes; Ginnie enhanced files
Comments: Free for internal use, need a commercial license for external distribution (starts at 10k each)

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: House or condo securing loan
Description: Physical real estate asset that serves as collateral for a mortgage loan, with location and property type that tie into housing fundamentals and HPI.
KeyAttributes: property_id; property_type; unit_count; occupancy_status; initial_appraisal_value; orig_CLTV; geo_id (zip/county/MSA)
TypicalSources: GSE disclosures; public records; AVM providers; FHFA geo mapping
Comments: Free for internal use, need a commercial license for external distribution (starts at 10k each)

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: FICO 720-740; LTV 70-80; owner occupied; CA
Description: Aggregated borrower bucket representing a group of loans with similar risk attributes used for cohort based analytics rather than individual borrowers.
KeyAttributes: cohort_id; FICO_bucket; LTV_bucket; DTI_bucket; occupancy; purpose; region
TypicalSources: Constructed from loan data using internal rules
Comments: Free for internal use, need a commercial license for external distribution (starts at 10k each)

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Scheduled and actual payments at pool or tranche level
Description: Individual cashflow events, including scheduled and realized principal, interest, fees, losses and recoveries associated with a pool or tranche.
KeyAttributes: cf_id; source_node_id (pool/tranche); cashflow_type (sch_prin; act_prin; interest; fee; loss; recovery); amount; currency; payment_date
TypicalSources: Pool factor files; remittance reports; trustee reports; vendor cashflow engines
Comments: Calculate it based on loan details, create an internal model of cash flows

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Loan status at a date - current; 30dpd; 60dpd; 90dpd; FC; REO; paid_off; modified
Description: Categorical state of a loan at a point in time describing delinquency, default, foreclosure, REO or payoff status.
KeyAttributes: loan_id; status_code; status_date; loss_status_flag
TypicalSources: GSE loan level disclosures; servicer performance data; non agency remittance reports
Comments: Free for internal use, need a commercial license for external distribution (starts at 10k each)

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: CPR; SMM; CDR; CRR at pool or cohort level by month; refi vs turnover split where available
Description: Aggregated measures of prepayment and default activity that summarize how quickly principal is returning, and distinguish refinance driven vs turnover driven prepayments where possible.
KeyAttributes: metric_type (CPR/SMM/CDR/CRR); value; period; scope_id (pool_id or cohort_id); refi_share; turnover_share
TypicalSources:
ICE/eMBS

Derived from factors; Ginnie Global Markets Analysis; FHFA prepayment monitoring; vendor prepayment analytics

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Delinquency rate; serious delinquency; foreclosure rate; loss rate; loss severity
Description: Aggregated measures of credit performance and loss for a pool or cohort, tracking the build up and resolution of credit stress.
KeyAttributes: metric_type (delinquency_rate/serious_dq/foreclosure_rate/loss_rate/severity); value; period; scope_id (pool_id or cohort_id)
TypicalSources: Loan level disclosures; remittance reports; credit analytics vendors

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: TRACE trade in a specific MBS CUSIP
Description: Individual secondary market transaction with price, size, time, and counterparty type information used to infer liquidity and market levels.
KeyAttributes: trade_id; cusip; price; size; trade_datetime; side (dealer_customer/interdealer); counterparty_type; venue
TypicalSources: FINRA TRACE MBS data products

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Dealer quote on TBA or specified pool
Description: Indicative or firm bid or ask from a dealer or platform for a given TBA contract or specified pool, used to measure market levels and payups.
KeyAttributes: quote_id; symbol (cusip/TBA); bid; ask; size; quote_time; source
TypicalSources: Bloomberg; Tradeweb; dealer runs

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Daily close price; yield; Z spread; OAS; duration; convexity for each security or TBA coupon stack
Description: Time series of derived pricing and risk measures for a security or TBA, used in valuation, risk and relative value analysis.
KeyAttributes: security_id; metric_type (price/yield/OAS/Z/duration/dv01/convexity); value; date
TypicalSources: Bloomberg; Refinitiv; Yield Book; Intex; internal curve engine

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Volume; number_of_trades; bid ask spread; turnover at security, cohort or index level
Description: Aggregated statistics describing how actively a security or cohort trades and how tight the market is, used to quantify liquidity risk and transaction costs.
KeyAttributes: scope_id (security/cohort/index); metric_type (volume/trade_count/spread/turnover); value; date
TypicalSources: TRACE aggregates; vendor liquidity analytics; internal calculations

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Unemployment rate; nonfarm payrolls; CPI; PCE; GDP; ISM; retail sales; industrial production; consumer confidence
Description: Macro economic time series that describe the overall growth, inflation, labor market and business cycle backdrop driving rates and credit risk.
KeyAttributes: series_id; name; domain=macro; subcategory (labor/inflation/growth/sentiment); frequency; units; source_code
TypicalSources: BLS; BEA; ISM; Conference Board; FRED

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Housing starts; building permits; completions; new home sales; existing home sales; inventory; months of supply
Description: Housing activity indicators that track construction, sales volumes and inventory, used to gauge housing supply and turnover risk.
KeyAttributes: series_id; name; domain=housing; subcategory (starts/sales/inventory); frequency; units; geo_coverage
TypicalSources: US Census; NAR; HUD; FRED

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: FHFA House Price Index (national/state/MSA/zip for GSE eligible loans); S&P CoreLogic Case Shiller indexes
Description: House price index series that measure home value changes across geographies and segments, used to model CLTV paths and collateral strength.
KeyAttributes: series_id; name; domain=housing; subcategory=home_prices; frequency; geo_resolution (national/state/MSA/zip); index_base_year; units
TypicalSources: FHFA HPI datasets; S&P CoreLogic Case Shiller; FRED mirrors

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: MBA Weekly Mortgage Applications Survey - Purchase index; Refi index; Composite index; Mortgage Credit Availability Index (MCAI); rate lock series if used
Description: Mortgage market activity and underwriting indicators capturing demand for new loans and refis and the ease or tightness of credit conditions.
KeyAttributes: series_id; name; domain=mortgage; subcategory (applications/credit_availability/rate_locks); frequency (weekly/monthly); units
TypicalSources: MBA; Optimal Blue or ICE for rate locks; FRED for some MBA series

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Total mortgage debt outstanding; share in agency MBS vs private label RMBS vs HELOCs; outstanding HELOC balances
Description: High level aggregates describing the size and composition of the mortgage system balance sheet, including agency share and other mortgage products.
KeyAttributes: series_id; name; domain=mortgage_system; subcategory (debt_stock/agency_share/heloc); frequency (quarterly); units
TypicalSources: Federal Reserve Z.1 Flow of Funds; Urban Institute Housing Finance Chartbook

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Primary mortgage rates - Freddie PMMS 30y fixed; 15y fixed; ARM rates; points and fees
Description: Survey based measures of average primary mortgage rates offered to borrowers, used to compute refi incentive and primary secondary spreads.
KeyAttributes: series_id; name; domain=mortgage; subcategory=primary_rates; frequency (weekly); units (percent)
TypicalSources: Freddie Mac Primary Mortgage Market Survey; FRED

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Fed funds target rate; effective fed funds; SOMA MBS holdings; QE/QT pace; Fed balance sheet totals
Description: Monetary policy and balance sheet series capturing policy stance and central bank presence in the MBS market.
KeyAttributes: series_id; name; domain=policy; subcategory (policy_rates/balance_sheet); frequency; units
TypicalSources: Federal Reserve H.4.1; NY Fed SOMA data; FRED

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Treasury yields by tenor (2y; 5y; 10y; 30y); swap rates; OIS curve
Description: Interest rate curve series across maturities and instruments used for discounting, hedge ratios and spread calculations.
KeyAttributes: series_id; name; domain=rates_curve; subcategory (UST/swap/OIS); frequency (daily); units (percent)
TypicalSources: US Treasury; swaps provider; Bloomberg; FRED for Treasuries

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Primary secondary spread (primary mortgage rate minus current coupon); MBS OAS vs Treasury; standard basis series
Description: Spread and basis series that link mortgage rates and MBS yields to risk free curves, capturing the mortgage basis and lender margins.
KeyAttributes: series_id; name; domain=mortgage_spread; frequency; units (basis_points)
TypicalSources: Constructed from PMMS and your curve/OAS engine; Bloomberg spread series

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: UNRATE value on 2025-01-01; HOUST value on 2025-01-01; FHFA HPI for CA on 2025-01-01
Description: Individual observation of a given indicator series at a specific date (and possibly geography), storing the numeric value and metadata.
KeyAttributes: observation_id; series_id; value; effective_date; revision_flag; geo_id (optional)
TypicalSources: Loaded from source APIs or files for each IndicatorSeries

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: 10y UST at 4.2 percent on 2025-01-01; 5y swap at 3.8 percent
Description: Point on a yield curve at a given date and tenor, used to reconstruct full curves for pricing and risk models.
KeyAttributes: curve_id; series_id; tenor; rate_type (UST/swap/OIS); value; date
TypicalSources: Treasury; swaps provider; vendor curves

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Fannie Mae; Freddie Mac; Ginnie Mae; private RMBS issuers
Description: Legal entities that issue MBS or RMBS deals and stand behind the securities structurally or via guarantees.
KeyAttributes: entity_id; name; role=issuer; country; regulator_id; LEI
TypicalSources: GSE data; SEC filings; LEI registries

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Wells Fargo; Rocket; non bank mortgage originators
Description: Entities that originate mortgage loans which later end up in securitized pools or whole loan portfolios.
KeyAttributes: entity_id; name; role=originator; channel_type (retail/wholesale/correspondent); country
TypicalSources: Public disclosures; HMDA; internal mapping

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Mr Cooper; Ocwen; bank servicers
Description: Entities responsible for collecting payments, managing delinquencies, and handling loss mitigation for mortgage loans.
KeyAttributes: entity_id; name; role=servicer; servicing_portfolio_stats
TypicalSources: Servicer reports; GSE data

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: BNY Mellon; Deutsche Bank
Description: Entities that act as trustees for securitization trusts and administer cashflows and reporting for investors.
KeyAttributes: entity_id; name; role=trustee
TypicalSources: Trustee and deal documentation

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: S&P; Moody's; Fitch
Description: Credit rating agencies that assign and monitor ratings on securitization tranches and other fixed income securities.
KeyAttributes: entity_id; name; role=rating_agency
TypicalSources: Rating reports; regulatory filings

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Banks; REITs; insurers; asset managers
Description: End investors that hold MBS and related securities, such as banks, insurance companies, REITs and asset managers.

TypicalSources: 13F filings; regulatory reports; internal holdings data

ExampleSeriesOrEntity: Primary dealers and MBS market makers
Description: Broker dealer firms that make markets and intermediate trading in MBS and TBA contracts.

TypicalSources: TRACE dealer codes; internal mapping

Description: Time dimension node representing a calendar date or period used to anchor all time series and events.
